title: For Sale:  AK 47 Arsenal SLR-101S
postcontent:
Arsenal SLR-101S Best of the best. If you know what it is you're interested. If you don't and you want an AK be sure to read below. These don't come available very often. It is in like new condition. 

I am selling an as new Bulgarian made Arsenal SLR-101S AK rifle, caliber 7.62x39mm. The SLR101 is made in Bulgaria and imported as a complete rifle. This means both the receiver and barrel are original Arsenal BG milspec. Rifle comes with 1 Bulgarian made 40rd magazine. The original Soviet Russian AK47 utilized a milled receiver from the late 1940s until the adoption of the less expensive and lighter AKM in 1959. Most other Warsaw Pact nations followed suit and switched from the milled AK47 to the stamped AKM. While Arsenal in Bulgaria did manufacture stamped rifles starting in the 1960s, it never abandoned the milled design and continued to update and modernize it. The Bulgarian military has been using these weapons for decades, in various configurations.
Back in 2001, Arsenal Inc. of NV in the USA imported a milled rifle from Arsenal of Bulgaria called the SLR101. This rifle had an original Bulgarian made milled receiver, as well as an original Bulgarian barrel. This line was discontinued 10 years ago and only in 2012 has Arsenal once again imported a batch of SLR101s. Arsenal has done the SA M7 line with a milled receiver, but with one key difference; the SA M series used a US made milled receiver and other US parts. The SLR101 is wholly made in Bulgaria and is imported into the US as a complete weapon. It is brought in without a bayonet lug and with a thumbhole stock, to get around import restrictions. Once in the country, Arsenal Inc. installs a proper butt stock, pistol grip, and muzzle brake. They also insure the rifle is capable of accepting any standard AK double stack, high capacity magazines. All parts are Bulgarian made, except for the required 922(r) ones. These parts are made in the USA by Arsenal, but to original Bulgarian specifications and include: the furniture set, trigger group, and muzzle brake.
Comparing the 2012 SLR101-13 to the 2001 SLR101s, the same manufacturing quality and fit and finish can be found. Since the 2001 rifles were sold during the 1994 Clinton AWB, they were not allowed to have either the removable muzzle device, threaded barrel, or bayonet lug. These modern SLR101 rifles though have all of these features as the AWB sunset in 2004.
This rifle features: original Arsenal of Bulgaria AK47 style milled receiver, original 16" long Cold Hammer Forged barrel with a chrome lined bore, standard 14mm threads on the end of the barrel, side-mount on the receiver for optics, a smooth double hook trigger, intermediate length polymer butt stock, milspec polymer hand guards with steel heat shield, standard military pistol grip, and the ability to accept any standard AK47/AKM magazines and drums. These milled Arsenals are known for their reliability and trouble-free service; but if it does have any problems, it is fully covered under Arsenal's warranty. It has been a decade since any milled receiver rifles have come in from Bulgaria and I don't think I am out of line in saying they are some of the finest AK pattern rifles ever produced. All moving parts work smoothly; the rifle is very accurate, durable, and great looking. 
Asking $1,200 O.B.O. Need to sell but won't just give it away, so no low ballers please. 
Pictures can be send by request. 
Thanks for looking and God Bless.

Up for sale is 1000 rounds of once fired .223 / 5.56 Lake City (LC) Military Brass. Brass has been decapped, swaged, resized, trimmed and polished clean in SS Pin media. All of these casings are LAKE CITY (LC) NATO military surplus.  

WE SHIP TO ALL 50 STATES.  Shipping is a flat rate of $12.35. Payment must be received prior to shipping. 

The following forms of payment are accepted: USPS Money Order, Cashiers Check, Credit Card (add 3% to cover CC fees), Paypal (add 3% to cover PayPal processing fee), or Personal Check. Personal Checks will be held 10 business days or until clear. A $35.00 fee will be assessed for returned Personal Checks. 

Brass will ship the following day, with the exception of Sunday, after funds have been received. Your tracking number will be emailed to your account as soon as USPS accepts the package for shipment. 

If you want more or less brass, or dirty brass, just ask!  Dirty/unprocessed brass sells for $60/1000 rounds, cleaned/polished unprocessed brass is $70/1000 rounds.  5.56 blanks are available for $35/1000 (great for conversion to 300 Blackout!)

We also offer Hornaday .224 55gr bullets for $90/1000 with your purchase ($100 if buying w/o cases).  Available in either Full Metal Jacket with Boat Tail or Soft Point with Flat Back.

I will combine shipping on larger orders. 

United States Citizens ONLY.  We purchased this brass from the US Army and are prohibited from selling to non citizens or exporting.

title: For Sale:  Millett Long Range Scope
postcontent:
Second Generation LR-S scope for long range shooting. The extreme-duty, extended-range LR-S tactical riflescope, by Millett is massively built with a one-piece 30mm tube and 56mm objective, the LR-S delivers superior brightness and outstanding repeatable accuracy with the largest long-range weapons, including those chambered for the 50 BMG and 338 Lapua. Precision controls with 1/4 MOA adjustment

•	Telepower: 4-16x56
•	Paralax Adjustment (OA): 0-200 on to infinity - 10
•	Objective Lens Diameter: 56mm
•	Eye Relief: 3”+
•	Tube Diameter: 30mm
•	Optics: Fully Multi-Coated
•	Reticle: Glass-Etched Cross-Bar
•	Sun Shade: 4 inches


I used this scope on My AR-10 (308 version of the AR-15) with my 20 inch stainless bull barrel. I normally shot out to 1000 yards in competition with this rifle and always did very well. The scope was mounted on the scope for 8 years and stored in my climate controlled safe room (yea I have an entire vaulted room that stores my firearms – there are a lot of them) The room is kept at 15% humidity and 70 degrees at all times, which is perfect for gun storage. The gun was and scope were never in the rain, and both were cleaned and put away promptly after each use. This scope has never seen hunting nor has it ever been exposed to any harsh elements. It has never been dropped and it has only been mounted and dismounted one time each. The rings are extremely heavy duty Millett (came with the scope) 30MM and they were matched and mounted at the Millett factory. They are designed to fit any picatinny rail or standard dove tail base or picatinny rail. The scope when brand new was $469.00 8 years ago. There is no damage nor is there any fungus or scratches. You will be very impressed when you see the scope. It is best suited for long range or “sniper” type rifles but will be great on anything such as a .223 or 22-250 varmint rifle (which is what I was going to put it on). The scope comes with flip up lens protectors (aftermarket) You can call with any questions… leave a message and I will get back to you. I am currently selling a lot of gun related stuff as I am moving overseas and can’t take it all with me. I will return your call with a short period if you do not get me directly. I am asking $200.00. REDACTED David
